cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the downlink of a wireless network and considers the maximum total timely throughput of the network. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the fundamental limits of timely throughput in wireless networks, which involves the study of information transmission and processing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes algorithms and policies for maximizing timely throughput in wireless networks, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions real-time video traffic, which is a type of multimedia traffic. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper deals with maximizing the timely throughput of wireless networks, which is related to performance optimization.
